Barry Spatz:<br><br>
I risked my life once to evacuate a wounded V.C. POW.  No one gave a shit if he lived or died, except me.  We had no friendly casualties at the time for me to evacuate.  I placed my life and the lives of my devoted crew on the line in bad weather and a serious combat situation to fly this man to adequate medical care.  I don't know if he lived or died, but I and my crew seemed to feel good about our effort as we returned to the battle site!<br>
I had enough respect for this communist soldier to recognize that he was no longer a threat to me or my people, I viewed him as a fellow human struggling to hold on to his life.<br>
You are not the type of individual who would risk discomfort, much less your life for anyone or anything!  The overwhelming impact of your cowardice upon yourself has caused you some serious psychiatric disorders and you need help!  You will never be a combat veteran...you missed your chance by fleeing!  However, it is not essential that you be a combat veteran to find self worth!  I suggest that you turn to God who is able and willing to love you regardless of your antics.  That simple revelation may start you on the journey to begin to love yourself in an acceptable manner..that someday you will be able to love others.  Without love for others, you will always be a hollow, ringing clarion of envy and abasement!<br>
Please seek some professional help and stay off this site where you are causing more damage to yourself than you are to seasoned veterans, scholars, and leaders of men!<br><br>
Mustang Two Four
